  "text": "Our current results suggest that multiple genes involved in synaptic functioning are important for schizophrenia, provide support for the synaptic hypothesis of schizophrenia [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [18] and provide tentative evidence for the involvement of the biological mechanisms involved in intracellular signal transduction, excitability and cell adhesion and transsynaptic signaling molecules in schizophrenia.",
